      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a classic example of how government mandates directly squeeze small business margins. Increased labor costs force owners to either raise prices, which customers in smaller towns might resist, or cut back on hiring and services. This ultimately slows down the very local economic growth that proponents claim to support. Businesses need to be nimble, focusing on efficiency rather than absorbing unsustainable wage increases.",
